rComments: the content: hard. you actually have to put in the effort but if you do, you'll get a good grade. prof gives clear instructions and lectures are good. the 2 big assignments prepare you for midterm/exam so no surprises. only critique is almost always ran over time in lectures so some parts felt rushed. 10/10 prof, content is just tough for some

I had her for 3rd year Applied Statistical Analysis. The course itself is hard and she made it much easier on everyone. Smart (and funny!) woman who knows her stuff. Made what could have been very dry lectures about stats more interesting and put people who were nervous about 'doing math' at ease. Fair prof.

I think the prof added that first comment.I will give her this, she does know her stuff but she SPEEDS through lectures and acts high and mighty/ doesn't offer help. I ended up teaching myself by the textbook. not the worst but I do dislike profs that think they are better than everyone. you will see what I mean if you choose her!!

Prof. Rippeyong is very witty and is an excellent lecturer. Stats is full of dry material, but she adds in her own unique flavour that makes it bearable. She lightens the mood by playing music related to the theme of the lecture before every class. She really bends over backwards to make sure you understand the material. Awesome professor!!!!
